Connecting Grassroot Initiative(CGI) Is a volunteer group that comprises of notable Nollywood actors and actresses who believe in Asiwaju Bola Ahmed Tinubu/Kashim Shettima presidency and re-election of Governor Babajide Sanwo-Olu /Obafemi Hamzat for the Second term.

As part of the Connecting Grassroot Initiative’s(CGI) plan to move from one local government to another with the aim of spreading the gospel of ASIWAJU /SHETTIMA and SANWO-OLU /HAMZAT to lagosians.  The campaign train moved from IKEJA LOCAL GOVERNMENT over the weekend with door to door campaign. Their soul winning campaign saw many trooped out to show their love and support for the ruling APC.

They will be moving from one local government area to another till they cover the entire Lagos State.

CGI !!! ON APC MANDATE, WE STAND

@cgi_2023  Supports Sanwo...

Tell me what your Governor has done and show me if he has performed better than Sanwo-Olu- Bigsam @officialsamolatunji1 

Earlier today at the barber shop, a young man from a PDP governed state said expressly that Governor Sanwo-Olu hasn't done anything in office. 
Shocked, I asked if the Universities in his home state joined the protracted ASUU strike in 2022. He said, "yes." When I told him that Lagos State University, Ojo and other state-owned higher institutions didn't join the strike for a day due to Governor  Sanwo-olu's leadership skills and foresight of his Education management team led by Tokunbo Wahab, he found it hard to believe. A simple online search cleared his doubts. And the Polytechnic and Colleges of Education were upgraded to universities (All under four years).

There are many doubters like this guy out there. Quick to pooh-pooh Sanwo-Olu's landmark achievements in 4 years while their home state governors can't point at any tangible achievements after 4 or 8 years in office.

Let’s give Sanwo-Olu his garlands. He has done well and he will do more. 

I've compiled a list of Sanwo-olu's achievements after four years in office. Suffice to say most governors can't achieve same in 8 years.

Come Saturday March 11th, Sanwo-Olu @jidesanwoolu has my vote again.

Cc @kingmcoluomo
